File: Peter Moyo was suspended in May and later fired as CEO of Old Mutual. JOHANNESBURG - Old Mutual is planning to appeal the South Gauteng High Court ruling, ordering the reinstatement of its axed CEO. Peter Moyo won a bid against the insurance company to be temporarily reinstated with immediate effect, and his dismissal declared unlawful. READ: Peter Moyo to get his job back Meanwhile Old Mutual insists it followed sound governance principles when it took the decision to fire Moyo. The insurer also says it gave a valid notice under his employment contract. Old Mutual suspended Moyo in May and later fired him as CEO last month, citing a conflict of interest in his personal business matters. Ian Williamson will continue as interim CEO.